\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 15. Q. pedunculiflora} C. Koch, {\i Linnaea}{\b  22:} 324 (1849) ({\i Q. haas} auct. eur., non Kotschy). Like {\b 14}({\b b}) but leaves somewhat glaucous above and with persistent yellow-grey tomentum beneath; petiole up to 20 mm; involucral scales verrucose, more concrescent, and pubescent with yellowish hairs.{\i  S.E. Europe}. Bu Gr Ju Rm ?Rs(K) Tu. ({\i E. Anatolia, S.W. Caucasus.})
