\pard\f0\fs28 {\b Q. sicula} Borzi in Lojac., {\i Fl. Sic.}{\b  2}({\b 2}): 374 (1907) ({\i Q. borzii} A. Camus), from Sicilia, is said to have a larger cupule and fruit 30-35 × 22-28 mm, but is otherwise similar to {\b 19}. It has not been reported recently.
\par

