\pard\f0\fs28 {\b Q. cerrioides }Willk. & Costa, {\i Linnaea }{\b 30:} 123 (1859), from E. Spain, with toothed, ovate leaves usually more than 6 cm, is probably derived from {\b 19} by hybridization with {\b 21}.
\par

