\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 20. Q. canariensis} Willd., {\i Enum. Pl. Horti Berol. }975 (1809). Semi-evergreen tree up to 30 m; twigs and young leaves densely floccose-tomentose, eventually glabrescent. Leaves 6-18 cm, elliptic-ovate, with 9-14 pairs of subacute teeth, glaucous beneath lateral veins parallel; petiole 8-30 mm. Peduncle short; lower scales of involucre ovate-lanceolate, tuberculate, the upper much smaller, loosely appressed.{\i  Spain and S. Portugal.} Hs Lu.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 In N. Spain extensively hybridized with {\b 19}.
